    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="894"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d894">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.6363/33: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McGoodwin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-24T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Your 45 June 11, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>Carib Syndicate, New York Corporation, represents to Department that it owns 25
                    per cent Colon Development Company and that it owns besides, by assignment from
                    Andres Vigas, original concessionaire, and his associates, Julian Arroya and
                    Joseph Paris, certain vendors’ rights reserved on sale to Colon Development
                    Company.</p>
                <p>Decision Supreme Court would apparently destroy Carib Syndicate equitable rights
                    in properties covered by concession, and therefore this Government would be
                    pleased if in disposition of properties covered by concession such equitable
                    rights could be recognized and protected.</p>
                <p>Inform Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
